<br>
But I've never posted on them either and here's what I think.<br>
(Which has been said in various ways by various people)<br>
<br>
The AC &quot;soft cap&quot; is determined by in mobs attack value.  Once you have more ac than the mob has attack, extra ac doesn't really help you any.  For example, if the only mobs in the world were fire beetles, then people would think that there is no benefit to having ac above say 100 (and they would be right).  This is because you have already reduced the mobs attack capability to its minimum.  I believe for normal mobs (&lt;60), their attack value doesn't exceed ~1250.  That's why there seems to be a &quot;soft cap&quot; at that value.  Uber mobs, on the other hand, may have attack values of say 4000.  So in that case, 1500ac would be better than 1250ac, but the mobs attack would still be 2500+ more than your ac.  So more than likely it would hit you for around max with almost every hit anyways.  Which makes me believe you should go for hp items when tanking uber mobs maximizing the effectiveness of CH (unless you can get your ac up to 4000 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  Even if there were no caps at all, I don't think you would see any difference between 1,000,000ac and 2,000,000ac because you would be so much higher than any existing mobs attack.  So there would be a practical cap based on the mobs in the world.<br>
<br>
This is just what I think; sorry if I repeated anything anyone else said.  We have so many tests coming up with different results, I think if they were all done on the same mob they would all get the same results (but they are not).  I have no logs or data to back this up (I couldn't figure out the mobs attack anyways), but it makes sense to me.  I'm just trying to make a helpful suggestion.  Besides, I don't think anyone will ever be satisfied with tests or posted logs... best thing for anyone is to go out and try tanking mobs with different ac and do what seems best to you.  Nothing can substitute for real experience. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=1011.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=1011.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=1011.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=1011.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=1011.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a> <b>6</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showPrevMessage?topicID=1011.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showNextMessage?topicID=1011.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=101><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.emailToFriend?topi